sub_title: MD/PhD Candidate Department of Cardiology at UMCG
summary:
My journey towards pursuing my academic goals started when I moved from Suriname to the Netherlands in 2018 to study Medicine at the University of Groningen.

Alongside obtaining my medical degree, I have a strong ambition to contribute to scientific research. With my current position as MD/PhD candidate at the Department of Cardiology at the University Medical Centre Groningen, I am working on projects focusing on elucidating the role of obesity in heart failure.
